So, just to get this out of the way, I have two main categories for projects:
These are passion projects and normal projects.

Now, these sound similar, and a slip of the tongue might happen here or there,
but there is a definite difference between the two!

Passion projects are projects I pour my love into. I do my best to make their
development good and generally usable, as they are designed for not just me,
but also the public! I strive to keep them in functional working order, and I
do my best to ensure their functionality. Their AI use is limited, as I care
about my projects having originated mainly from me. Because of this, I will
only be using AI on them for debugging, research, or minor instances as I see
fit. If the passion project you are looking at does not have a license
specified, then assume MIT (shown below).

TL;DR:
✅ I care for these a lot
✅ I design these with the public in mind
✅ I update these and patch bugs;
✅ I build almost everything myself without AI
✅ I strive to learn from these
✅ CONSTRUCTIVE criticism is highly recommended, please and thank you
🪧 Refer to the MIT licese below for the legal stuff


Now, on the other side of things...

Normal projects are little things I don't really care about too much. They're
not designed to be user-friendly or able to be run on all systems, just user-
friendly enough for me to find some use in them. While they may be fun, I
won't be updating them. Feel free to make forks of it or use it elsewhere at
any time, I won't stop you, and you don't need to ask for permission; it's all
public domain. However, because I only care about the output rather than the
process of growth, I will be using AI. All normal projects are public domain;
refer to Unlicensed (shown below)

TL;DR:
❌ I don't care for these too much
❌ I design these with nobody in particular in mind
❌ I won't be updating or patching these;
❌ The majority of the code is probably bad and also probably AI
❌ I don't really learn from these, I just want the output they give
❌ Don't hate on me for using AI here, I really don't care about these, sorry
🪧 Refer to the unlicensed licese below for the legal stuff


Thank you for being the one of five people
